          .bodyText
            p About myself I’ll say this:
            p I was born and raised in Portland, OR, became an adult in New York City, have spent long stretches in South Africa and France, and currently reside on a farm outside of Nashville, Tennessee.
            p I’ve worked in neurobehavioral research labs studying postpartum depression using FMRI technology, as a academic tutor for high-achieving students, as an English teacher in elementary schools in France, in book publishing as an editor, production manager, and designer, in advertising as a project manager and at a tech start-up as a product manager, only to find myself back in the classroom studying to become a software developer.
            p What I've discovered in all of these lives, is that I love to learn, and that I love to build. And it are these passions that brought me to software development – a discipline that is the perfect marriage of my analytical and creative brain.
            p In software development, I’ve found the opportunity to marry my creative brain with my analytical brain. This has been a dream I didn’t know I was chasing, am I so grateful to have stumbled upon.
            p As a developer my interests lie in creating software that addresses the changing economy, including how people earn money, take care of themselves and their health, and live lives of their own choosing. I believe software should be as intuitive as it is functional, accessible to everyone, and create value for the user.
